The paper is primarily focused on the development of a logical framework for computability, which falls under the category of mathematical logic (cs.LO). However, the paper also discusses complexity theory and its relationship to the CoL framework, which could potentially place it in the categories of computational complexity (cs.CC) and programming languages (cs.PL). Additionally, the paper discusses the application of the CoL framework to constructive applied theories, which could potentially place it in the categories of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
